  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and coordinate all aspects of Electrical, Instrumentation, Control, and Automation (EICA) operations for water and wastewater treatment projects, driving project success through effective team management, technical execution, and stakeholder collaboration.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead planning, organization, direction, coordination, and control of all project operations to achieve defined objectives on cost, time, quality, and technical standards</li><li>Monitor project progress actively and resolve site and technical issues promptly to maintain project timelines and quality</li><li>Manage and develop a team of EICA Engineers specializing in Electrical, Instrumentation, Control, and Automation design for water and wastewater treatment projects</li><li>Oversee procurement, costing, and timely delivery of electrical software and hardware to support project requirements</li><li>Direct automation programming activities ensuring compliance with clients’ technical specifications and project standards</li><li>Coordinate control panel and equipment assembly, testing, and installation at construction sites to ensure operational readiness</li><li>Lead a team of Engineers and Technicians in diagnosing and resolving EICA system breakdowns to minimize downtime</li><li>Facilitate technical meetings with Clients, Consultants, and Sub-Contractors to clarify requirements and coordinate project arrangements</li><li>Maintain systematic records of EICA designs, drawings, and project documentation for accuracy and accessibility</li><li>Provide technical support and assistance to the Sales Department and Maintenance Team to enhance service delivery and client satisfaction</li><li>Execute other ad-hoc assignments as required to support project and organizational goals</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree in Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication), Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 12 years of experience working in membrane-based water treatment plants</li><li>Proficiency in Schneider, Siemens, and Allen-Bradley software for automation and control systems</li><li>Strong knowledge of SCADA and HMI systems for monitoring and control</li><li>Excellent communication skills to effectively engage with diverse stakeholder</li><li>Demonstrates strong team spirit and positive interpersonal skills to foster collaboration and a productive work environment</li></ul>",
